! `<$calc>` widget — examples

!! Basic arithmetic & number formatting

| Expression | `locale="en"` (default) | `locale="fr"` |h
| `<$calc>1 + 2 * 3</$calc>` | <$calc>1 + 2 * 3</$calc> | <$calc locale="fr">1 + 2 * 3</$calc> |
| `<$calc>1 000 000 / 3</$calc>` (thousands space) | <$calc>1 000 000 / 3</$calc> | <$calc locale="fr">1 000 000 / 3</$calc> |
| `<$calc>2^10</$calc>` | <$calc>2^10</$calc> | <$calc locale="fr">2^10</$calc> |
| `<$calc>√144</$calc>` (√ unicode) | <$calc>√144</$calc> | |
| `<$calc>∛27</$calc>` (∛ unicode) | <$calc>∛27</$calc> | |
| `<$calc>2² + 3²</$calc>` (superscripts) | <$calc>2² + 3²</$calc> | |
| `<$calc>½ + ¼</$calc>` (vulgar fractions) | <$calc>½ + ¼</$calc> | |
| `<$calc>π * 2</$calc>` (π unicode) | <$calc>π * 2</$calc> | <$calc locale="fr">π * 2</$calc> |
| `<$calc>τ / 2</$calc>` (τ = 2π) | <$calc>τ / 2</$calc> | |

!! Notation modes

| Expression | Result |h
| `<$calc notation="scientific">1234</$calc>` | <$calc notation="scientific">1234</$calc> |
| `<$calc notation="scientific" locale="fr">1234</$calc>` | <$calc notation="scientific" locale="fr">1234</$calc> |
| `<$calc notation="engineering">1234567</$calc>` | <$calc notation="engineering">1234567</$calc> |
| `<$calc notation="fixed" precision="2">3.14159</$calc>` | <$calc notation="fixed" precision="2">3.14159</$calc> |
| `<$calc notation="auto">0.000001 / 10</$calc>` (auto triggers below 1e-6) | <$calc notation="auto">0.000001 / 10</$calc> |
| `<$calc notation="fixed">0.000001 / 10</$calc>` (fixed, no scientific) | <$calc notation="fixed">0.000001 / 10</$calc> |
| `<$calc notation="bin">42</$calc>` | <$calc notation="bin">42</$calc> |
| `<$calc notation="oct">42</$calc>` | <$calc notation="oct">42</$calc> |
| `<$calc notation="hex">255</$calc>` | <$calc notation="hex">255</$calc> |
| `<$calc notation="hex">-255</$calc>` (negative accepted) | <$calc notation="hex">-255</$calc> |
| `<$calc notation="bin">3.7</$calc>` (non-integer truncated silently) | <$calc notation="bin">3.7</$calc> |

⚠️ bin/oct/hex: `locale` and `precision` are ignored. Non-integer values are truncated silently by math.js (`3.7` → `3`). Unit results produce an error — use `number(expr, unit)` to extract the numeric value first.

!! KaTeX rendering

| Expression | `show="result"` | `show="formula"` | `show="full"` |h
| `sqrt(x^2 + 1)` | <$calc>sqrt(x^2 + 1)</$calc> | <$calc show="formula">sqrt(x^2 + 1)</$calc> | <$calc show="full">sqrt(4)</$calc> |
| `(a+b)/c` | | <$calc show="formula">(a+b)/c</$calc> | |
| `pi * r^2` | | <$calc show="formula">pi * r^2</$calc> | <$calc show="full">pi * 5^2</$calc> |

Block display (`mode="block"`):

<$calc show="full" mode="block">sqrt(3^2 + 4^2)</$calc>

