!! Variables via scope tiddler

''Prerequisite:'' create a tiddler titled `MyVars` with this content:

```
r: 5
h: 10
density: 2.7
```

Then:

| Expression | Result |h
| `<$calc scope="MyVars">π * r^2</$calc>` (circle area) | <$calc scope="MyVars">π * r^2</$calc> |
| `<$calc scope="MyVars">π * r^2 * h</$calc>` (cylinder volume) | <$calc scope="MyVars">π * r^2 * h</$calc> |
| `<$calc scope="MyVars">density * π * r^2 * h</$calc>` (mass) | <$calc scope="MyVars">density * π * r^2 * h</$calc> |

!! Variables via inline scope

| Expression | Result |h
| `<$calc scope="{r: 3, h: 10}">pi * r^2 * h</$calc>` | <$calc scope="{r: 3, h: 10}">pi * r^2 * h</$calc> |
| `<$calc scope="{a: 1.5, b: 2.5}">sqrt(a^2 + b^2)</$calc>` | <$calc scope="{a: 1.5, b: 2.5}">sqrt(a^2 + b^2)</$calc> |

!! BigNumber precision

| Expression | `calcPrec="float"` | `calcPrec="64"` |h
| `1e13 + 1.23456789 - 1e13` | <$calc>1e13 + 1.23456789 - 1e13</$calc> | <$calc calcPrec="64">1e13 + 1.23456789 - 1e13</$calc> |
| `0.3 - 0.1 - 0.1 - 0.1` | <$calc>0.3 - 0.1 - 0.1 - 0.1</$calc> | <$calc calcPrec="64">0.3 - 0.1 - 0.1 - 0.1</$calc> |

!! Error messages & debouncing

The widget waits 200 ms after the last change before showing an error. Examples:

| Expression | Message |h
| `<$calc>sqrt(</$calc>` | <$calc>sqrt(</$calc> |
| `<$calc>1 / 0</$calc>` | <$calc>1 / 0</$calc> |
| `<$calc>sqt(4)</$calc>` | <$calc>sqt(4)</$calc> |
| `<$calc>1 +</$calc>` | <$calc>1 +</$calc> |
| `<$calc silence="yes">not_a_function(1)</$calc>` (silence → blank) | <$calc silence="yes">not_a_function(1)</$calc> |
